content.description: Climb up Arete with out going to the large right side pull.  Top outs the crux but the right hand is pretty sharp too.  going up direct changes the problem a lot with only cutting out one hand, you have to move your left to a worse hold and can't use the better right foot that is to far over.

content.description: Starting under the boulder pull directly on to the face after the roof. Avoid the arete on both sides and use only face holds. Good slots to a sharp pocket.
Start left corner of Cube and go up.

content.description: Start on right corner of the cube, get the foot, work left across the lip and up. Staying off any other boulders.

content.description: Climb the Right side of the boulder starting under the small roof. Use the Right Arete and some face holds to top out. Easy Route.

A Bit Contrived, but start under the cave and use the face hold on the lip and the slot to move to the left arete. Bump up left arete and swing feet over to eventually top out. Hidden Heel toe cam to make the move easier
A handful of nice problems on clean, solid rock, a little separated from the main cluster of Plan B.
